Author: whotheff
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: I just red the walpaper and I'm impressed. This is very close to how I imagine the both fast and scalable blockchain. However, after tortureing  Dmitry on Discord with questions, now I have more of them   1. In whitepaper you are speaking of proxy nodes and data storage nodes. Can I run such nodes, or they are regular nodes which are used with these special purpouse only?  2. After I register on Metagather.org and claim the free 1000 lended coins for forging (your word for staking), can I receive also more coins if my node is proxy or storage type?  3. If I run a full wallet, do I receive more coins? (is there an option to run a full node?)  4. When I registered it, I never received a private key for my wallet. Just a public one and a file which I don't know what do do with. Is it some kind of replacement of private key and if yes, can it be used via other, different wallet software?  4. The MHC coin is perfect for mobile devices, android TV boxes, old tablets, phones, Raspberry PIs and various IoT devices. Since it is not mining, it does not put stress on such devices so it can run peacefully on them.  Do you plan releasing software for Android platform?  5. Mobile wallet?  6. How can I find out what type of node I have?  a) Core b) Verification c) Peer  7. Please simplify the navigation of the wallet interface and add an uptime timer.

Author: maxwelfox
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Hello! Good to see you with us! Sorry for making you wait!  1. At this moment there are two roles that anyone can run:  - Peer Node  How to run peer node you can read here - https://metahash.readme.io/docs/server-setup  - Infrastructure Torrent node  How to run it, read here - https://metahash.readme.io/docs/infrustructure-torrent-node-setup  You can read more about our network structure in our yellow paper - https://static.metahash.org/docs/MetaHash_YellowPaper_EN.pdf?v=6    2. #MetaGather referral program does not include this feature. You have to buy the coins themselves or ask someone to delegate 100k coins to your node  Anological story with infrastructural torrent node.   3. You can check the node rewards that getting now on unofficial explorer made by our community member - https://metawat.ch   4. #MetaGather referral program giving everyone an opportunity to try out forging (https://metahash.readme.io/docs/what-is-forging) process. The reward for forging is distributed randomly among all participants, and what is most interesting is that you can get (if you are lucky) every day for reward more than 70 thousand #MetaHashCoin as a reward!   5. At the moment we have no plans to implement forging on mobile devices, only on desktop versions. The main focus of our team to achieve decentralized, really looking forward to it!  6. All information can be read in our information portal - https://metahash.readme.io/docs  7. Can you please tell me more about it ?   Also feel free to join our community chat in telegram  - https://t.me/metahash_eng

Author: whotheff
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: 7. So far the wallet has many features from Dapps to forging or just being a wallet. For a new user like me it was very unclear which is where. So I think menu re-organisation (from sombody not familiar with it) would help so simplify the interface. Also, the having one wallet provided by MHC for forging and another one where rewards from forging go is a pretty unclear concept.  I hope these will help improve it further!

Author: maxwelfox
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Greetings! #MetaGate is a custom tool for working and interacting with our network.  On our site for downloading #MetaGate, written "Your Gate to decentralized internet"  Link - https://metagate.metahash.org  And our cryptocurrency wallet is called #MetaWallet, by the way, soon we expect our wallet to be released on iOS as well! It will support currencies like BTC, ETH, and of course #MHC!  #MetaForging, is an application for interacting with our network, that's why it is located in the "#MetaApps" tab  In any case, we will take into account your feedback!   Quote Also, the having one wallet provided by MHC for forging and another one where rewards from forging go is a pretty unclear concept.  To run forging, you must have: Wallet with a balance of 1000 # MHC Installed #MetaGate on your device Manage to be online at least 4 hours a day.  The wallet that you are given with the frozen 1000 #MHC is the same as the one you created yourself, the only difference is that you do not know the password from it, so you can not make any transactions on it, only forge  So in fact you received a wallet (with frozen 1000 coins) for forging, which in any case will give you a reward, as well as an opportunity to win 77k #MHC. Not bad, yes?  Therefore, the reward comes to the wallet with frozen coins, then we transfer them to your wallet.  Thanks for your questions and feedback's! Very pleased to answer them!

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Dear community,  As you know recently we announced the new node role - Infrastructure Torrent. Right now this new role is published here: https://github.com/metahashorg/Node-InfrastructureTorrent We plan to spend a week or two helping node operators to explore the software and get feedback, then the new role will be activated.  Until then, the nodes reward poll will be distributed among proxy nodes only. After the full release of the Infrastructure Torrent Node, the distribution rules will be changed as announced here: https://news.metahash.org/?id=75  Important: the hardcap for proxy nodes will remain 10m #MHC for a while so all the participants have enough time to prepare for the reduction to 1m hardcap.

Body: Is there a sharding? So each Master & Verification shard contains & processes only one piece of blockchain.

Author: Gleb_Nikitin
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Yes and No. Incoming transactions are collected by multiple nodes and then sent to verification nodes that prepare sub-blocks for masters, masters merge the sub-blocks together, forge the block and seed to torrent nodes.  It's a very simplified story. Please check YP for a network diagram: https://static.metahash.org/docs/MetaHash_YellowPaper_EN.pdf?v=6

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: #MetaHashCoin is used to exchange for: transactions, data storage, app functions. You can also exchange #MHC to add a public address, to make your app listed in #MetaApp directory, to purchase ads in #MetaGate network and much more. And, of course, you can use it for forging.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: #MetaGate - is an open source interface using the #TraceChain protocol making it possible to work with #MetaApps and networks. Third-party developers can use the #MetaGate code to embed #MetaApps and #TraceChain/blockchain features into various applications and browsers.  #MetaGate consists of: 1. A multi-asset wallet that supports "light mode" without downloading the entire blockchain. Data comes from different sources of the decentralized network and is checked by the user. Of course, the wallet can work in "full node" mode or by selecting trusted nodes that have a copy of the #MetaChains application. (Private keys from all blockchains used will be stored only by the user.) The wallet which can be built from the source code in order to ensure the source code is validated by the community and that the wallet does, in fact, belong to the user. 2. A catalogue of decentralized applications and a browser to work with them. Any decentralized application built on #MetaHash can be accessed, not only through the standard internet domain but also via #MetaGate or it can be allocated to a separate program.  It would be better to download MetaGate and try it http://metagate.metahash.org/  Now you can try Android beta-version. iOS version will be available a little bit later.

(UK) - Bank4You Group Ltd  In the official registers Mr. Ganin is mentioned as the only officer of Metahash and of Clos Belmont Finance with sole signature right. The last fact is absolutely unusual because on the homepage of Clos Belmont Brian Hodge is named as CEO. A CEO without signature right?  https://cbfinance.ch/  In 8-12 Welbeck Way, London (Oracle House) there is Oracle Capital Group Ltd. located, a company also run by a sole officer (director) since June 2018, Yury Gantman , a British national with Russian and Israeli background.  https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/11417662/officers  https://orcap.co.uk/   Remark: Homepage only in English and Russian.  Like Clos Belmont Finance the last mentioned company has representative offices at Moscow and at Almaty/Kazakhstan. Both Moscow offices are headed by the same person: Nikita Goncharenko.  https://rocketreach.co/nikita-goncharenko-email_12342706  And surely by pure chance (?) the already mentioned obscure Bank4You Group Ltd also run by a sole officer (obviously a "front man" serving several other companies as a sole director) was located under the same address like Oracle Capital Group till it was deleted.  All facts pure coincidence or perhaps real connections?

Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: As per Swiss Law, the director of a local company must be the local resident. Founders listed on MetaHash website are also the founders of MetaHash AG and they used to work with Mr Ganin on various projects in the Swiss banking industry. Mr Ganin has a long experience in banking and truly believes that crypto industry will be powerfully supported by private and institutional investments. Thus he accepted an offer to lead Metahash project in Switzerland and became the local director for Metahash AG, Zug. In the coming weeks, the company will start to grow in staff and representation in Switzerland and will include several reputed local professionals from the crypto industry. Meanwhile, Clos Belmont Finance is a 14 year old multi-family office directed by the same person since 2009. Its main area of activity is external asset management and in this regard, the crypto industry is becoming one of investment focuses for a vast number of clients wishing to diversify their portfolios from pure vanilla banking products or private equity. There is no connection between the ICO of bank4u and Mr Kirill Ganin apart from the fact that he knows the UBO of the bank. He was no way connected to this ICO.  Also, please, check our article - https://medium.com/@themetahash/be-aware-information-attacks-c5bef88f1d4

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: DPoS  is actually very different from PoS. In DPoS, token hodlers don‚Äôt vote on the validity of the blocks themselves, but vote to elect delegates to do the validation on their behalf. There are generally between 21‚Äì100 elected delegates in a DPoS system. The delegates are shuffled periodically and given an order to deliver their blocks in. Having few delegates allows them to organize themselves efficiently and create designated time slots for each delegate to publish their block. If delegates continually miss their blocks or publish invalid transactions, the stakers vote them out and replace them with a better delegate.

Author: ShiftyTripster
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Okay... One more question. I made a transactions. Which path did it pass to be success?

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Here is what happens to a transaction:  - 0.2-0.4 seconds ‚Äì transmission between Peer Nodes. - The peer nodes maintain connections to slow clients and reject transactions with invalid signatures. - 0.8-1.2 seconds ‚Äì transmission to Verification Nodes. - Verification Nodes are organized into latency clusters with Masters/Slaves spanning geographically remote areas. - Verification Nodes check if there are enough funds to complete the transaction and carry the load associated with high-latency cross-continental peer connections. - 0.4-0.6 seconds ‚Äì transmission to Master Nodes. - The Master Nodes sync lost transactions and build a block from correct transactions. - 0.3-0.5 seconds ‚Äì Slaves check the validity of the block created by the Master Nodes and send it on to the torrents. - 0.6-0.8 seconds ‚Äì blocks from the nearest Slave Nodes are propagated via torrents, from which the client can collect transaction confirmation and current balances. - If torrents consider themselves invalid, they launch the process of role redistribution and verification of what Master/Slave Nodes have been corrupted.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: If coins were delegated to a compromised node that has been detected as performing malicious activity, the delegation is canceled automatically, and all coins are frozen for 10 days to exclude the possibility of any transfers or  redelegation. Coins remain in the ownership of their holder, but are unavailable for the next 10 days. So setting up fake nodes will not bring any profit to their owners.  And also the reliability of the node is regulated by the units of the trust. Moreover trust is used as weighting factor in role assignment and voting influence.  So, if you delegate coins to malicious node, in that case coins will recover in the ownership of their holder after 24 hours.  Malicious node will lost 6 month.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: These are Decentralized parsers of all popular blockchain platforms. In order for #MetaApps to immediately respond to events in any blockchain system, we will release decentralized parsers allowing the use of API to get balance info and transaction history from wallets across various blockchain platforms. This will allow applications to respond to different blockchain events and verify data accuracy by sending queries to network nodes.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: we have formula. Coin Holder Reward is calculated according to the following formula:  Coin Holder Reward = 0.5 * (Holder Coins At Stake/All Coins At Stake) * (ForgingPool + Commissions)  Description:  Holder Coins At Stake - Amount of coins delegated by the address holder All Coins At Stake - Amount of coins delegated by all the network addresses ForgingPool - Forging stimulation pool issued once every 24 hours for 10 years Commissions - All transactions or storage of data commissions received by the network during the past 24 hours  you can look at the details in our YP

Body: MultiPoS - Multiple Proof of Stake consensus model. In this model, multi-layered validation provides the basis for protecting a network against corruption. In cases when the central network entities, which generate blocks, appear to be corrupted, the rest of the network may vote to rebuild the network and to re-distribute the roles, thus, neutralizing the threat.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Assuming that the total reward for the block is 10k , the number of coins distributed among the voting participants is 5k (50%). Further, since Alisa has only 1/10 of all votes, she will receive 1/10 from 5k to 500 MHC, similarly with a reward for servers, they all receive a 4000MHC reward. Alice before Bob will have 1/10 of all voting tokens, so she will get 1/10 of the 4,000 MHC - 400 MHC. When Bob delegated 1,000,000 MHC to Alice, Bob was involved in the allocation of 5,000 MHC, and received 1/10 to 500 MHC, but he did not participate in the second allocation of 4,000 MHC, in that distribution it is believed that Alice has 2,000,000 coins, which is 2/10 of everything and therefore will receive 800 MHC. As a result, she receives 1300 MHC Bob will receive a total of 500MHC Hosts of peers will receive as Alisa, only they will participate in fewer votes, and therefore will earn less on a daily basis

Author: HeroSam911
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: I have a technical question. How validators will vote in your "Blockchain 4.0 aka Tracechain"?

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: In #TraceChain all validators vote simultaneously, rather than one by one. Therefore, if the core nodes create an invalid block and if the following validators reject it for some reason, the corruption check takes place and, where required, the network is rebuilt until consensus can be reached. At the same time, every new transaction is buffered at the verification node layer, so that processing of the buffer starts when the next valid block becomes available.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Yes, sure we have a formula. Coin Holder Reward is calculated according to the following formula:  Coin Holder Reward = 0.5 * (Holder Coins At Stake/All Coins At Stake) * (ForgingPool + Commissions)  Description:  Holder Coins At Stake - Amount of coins delegated by the address holder All Coins At Stake - Amount of coins delegated by all the network addresses ForgingPool - Forging stimulation pool issued once every 24 hours for 10 years Commissions - All transactions or storage of data commissions received by the network during the past 24 hours"

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: As of now, all network nodes are controlled by the #MetaHash team, therefore the system is deemed centralized. Decentralization of the new technology should go through a number of public tests, troubleshooting, and real-time changes. The #MetaHash team plans to support the network until it is fully decentralized and capable of self-development.  And also, we are using phased decentralization which will allow testing of each component one at a time with virtually no risk for the network.

If coins were delegated to a compromised node that has been detected as performing a malicious activity, the delegation is cancelled automatically, and all coins are frozen for 10 days to exclude the possibility of any transfers or redelegation. Coins remain in the ownership of their holder but are unavailable for the next 10 days.

Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Technology evolves and you have to support the renewal of yours blockchain. I lead to the fact that hard forks are inevitable. How will you overcome?

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: State blocks as an alternative to hard fork Since a State block contains a complete network snapshot, a hard fork is not necessary in cases of software updates. After network converts to new software, operations continue according to the same rules, until the next State block is sent. Activation of the new State block also activates the changes in the rules as required by the new software, allowing a simultaneous and smooth update process.  Details in our YP

Body: To achieve the optimal volume of data storage, archiving and blockchain multi-level high-speed validation, #MetaHash uses 3 types of blocks: Genesis block, State block, Micro block

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: State blocks as an alternative to hard fork. After network converts to new software, operations continue according to the same rules, until the next State block is sent. Activation of the new State block also activates the changes in the rules as required by the new software, allowing a simultaneous and smooth update process.

Author: lennymat86
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Thanks for the answer, but could you tell us more about them?

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: - Genesis block is a primary block, containing information on the initial release of coins and their distribution. - State block is a snapshot of a blockchain state. A State block is generated once per billion of transactions (250 GB) and requires a vote by all verification nodes. State blocks make it possible for verification nodes not to store older blocks, freeing space for new data, leaving old data in the data storage archive. - Micro block is generated every second based on Genesis or State blocks. Micro blocks are validated by a number of nodes that are available to run validation during the cycle, and checked by all validators upon their generation.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°

Author: HeroSam911
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Could you descibe in details, what is it MultiPoS?

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: MultiPoS - Multiple Proof of Stake consensus model. In this model, multi-layered validation provides the basis for protecting a network against corruption. In cases when the central network entities, which generate blocks, appear to be corrupted, the rest of the network may vote to rebuild the network and to re-distribute the roles, thus, neutralizing the threat.

Body: block-creating cores, while managing synchronization, are not static. They vary according to dynamic network parameters, and are not granted final validation rights.

Author: Awens
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: ICO Analysis: MetaHash Published on July 25, 2018 By Daniel Won  Team The team behind MetaHash is the same one behind AdSniper, an advertising company that according to MetaHash, built advertising networks capable of receiving and sending more than 100,000 requests per second, among other accomplishments. However, we weren‚Äôt able to independently verify these claims, and information on AdSniper is sparse (though this may be due to the fact that the company is Russian and we don‚Äôt have reliable English-based information about the company). Advisors MetaHash counts the following individuals amongst its advisors: Brock Pierce ‚Äì Pierce is a known name in the blockchain industry as the co-founder of Blockchain Capital (BCC), which is the company behind EOS (marketed via a different entity called Block.one), former Director of the Bitcoin Foundation, and one of the wealthiest individuals in cryptocurrency, with a net worth estimated between $700 million to $1 billion. However, Pierce‚Äôs Linkedin profile has no mention of MetaHash, which makes his involvement questionable. Verdict Below is a breakdown of the risks and growth potential of MetaHash. Risks     They claim that their mainnet can handle more than 60,000 transactions per second, but this claim doesn‚Äôt seem to be verifiable other than via their press material (-1)     Can‚Äôt find reliable background information on team or advisor involvement, e.g. Brock Pierce‚Äôs alleged involvement as an advisor for the project (-1) Growth Potential     They seem to have a very strong marketing and PR effort, with many users in their Telegram, a decent amount of Twitter followers, a decently long Bitcointalk thread, articles in many cryptocurrency publications, and high ratings from some ICO reviewers (+4) Disposition Although MetaHash scores decently in the hype department, lack of verifiable information about transaction throughput, team, and advisors make this one a pass. MetaHash receives a 2/10 Proof: https://hacked.com/ico-analysis-metahash/

Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: We can not grant a period at the discretion of the user, however, the regulation of the period will be based on the number of votes collected. There are 3 types of voting: "Extra" - the voting period is 24 hours Used only for directions where emergency voting may be necessary. With more than 10.000.000 votes against, the voting is put into the regime ¬´Fast¬ª.  "Fast" - the voting period is 1 week With more than 100,000,000 votes against the vote is set to the "standard" mode.  "Standard" - the voting period is 1 month Running a vote occurs publicly or by switching from the "fast" mode.  More details about the voting procedure, you can read in the WP.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Assuming that the total reward for the 10k block, the number of coins distributed among the voting participants is 5k (50%). Further, since Alice has only 1/10 of all votes, she will receive 1/10 from 5k to 500 MHC, Similarly, with a server reward, they all have a 4000 MHC reward, Alice will have Bobs 1/10 of all voting tokens, so she will get 1/10 of the 4,000 MHC - 400 MHC. When Bob delegated 1,000,000 MHC to Alice, Bob was involved in the allocation of 5,000 MHC, and received 1/10 to 500 MHC, but he did not participate in the second allocation of 4,000 MHC, in that distribution it is believed that Alice has 2,000,000 tokens, which is 2/10 of everything and therefore will receive 800 MHC. As a result, she receives 1300 MHC Bob will receive a total of 500 MHC  Hosts of peers will receive as Alice, only they will participate in fewer votes, and therefore will earn less than a day

Body: And how is the block distributed? How does he fall on the nodes?

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: MetaHash forging rewards distribution happens every 24 hours.  Reward Pool = 1/361 from yearly Forging Pool + Commissions from transactions in past 24 hours. So forgers get all rewards from pool and from transactions.  50% is distributed between coin holders that make stakes at Nodes. Your Share = your stake / all stakes from all people Your Reward = Your Share * Reward Pool  40% is distributed between people running Nodes Coins are deleted by Coin Owners to Nodes. It is possible to delegate Coins to a Node you own, but it is not obligatory. Node Reward = (delegated coins to a Node / all delegated coins) * ForceKoef * Trust ForceKoef is how useful a node is for network. More details will be in Yelllow Paper. Trust starts at 0.01 and gains 0.005 every day reaching 1 in 198 days.  If a Node lies it looses Trust and part of rewards for 198 days. Delegated coins are unlocked and owners must re-delegate.  10% is distributed between #MetaGates active for more than 4 hours in last 24 hours. Detailed spit is in WP.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: Each Node has an associated #MetaHash address. Every 24 hours rewards are calculated, all network nodes vote for them to be correct and they are send to all addresses that deserved rewards.

Body: Nevertheless, modern blockchain projects have their own disadvantages: the problem of scalability‚Ää‚Äî‚Ääthere is no possibility to increase the network performance; initially slow transaction processing speed; too power-hungry mining; the growing commission for processing the data chain and the lack of interest of users in future project development. All these problems are solved by the technologies developed by the #MetaHash team.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: #MetaHash is an original blockchain created from 0 in C/C++. Our goal was to improve delegated PoS consensus by optimising network sync by introducing roles and increase irreversible transaction creation speed by adding multi-layered verification on the way of the transaction sync. Our consensus is called multi-PoS because the block is created by multiple cores at the same time and verified by a tree of torrents upon it's journey to end-user. Doing this allowed us to sync 18 megabytes of data per second across hundreds or even thousands of nodes distributed around the globe in under 3 seconds resulting in over 50 000 tx/s. The reward system is also unique. There is no limit on delegates except the need to collect enough votes and rewards are distributed between all participants even the smallest ones.

Author: 247mining
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: #MetaHash is a Next-Generation Network based on the #TraceChain Protocol for sharing Digital Assets and a Platform for Creating and Managing Decentralised Apps and Services in Real-Time The #MetaHash Network consists of 4 Integral Elements:  - #Tracechain: Solution to Speed -> An introduction to an efficient way of processing more transactions in a fraction of just 3 seconds.   - #MetaApps -> The Core code of #MetaApps optimises the protection of application copies based on resources and financing of Node owners connected to the network. Any developer can create and publish an app in #MetaApps, and #MHC holders decide by Open Vote whether or not to approve it.   - #MetaGate -> An Open Source platform under #Tracechain protocol allowing us to operate with #MetaApps and networks. Using #MetaGate code, will  help us to embed #MetaApps and #Tracechain features into apps and browsers.  - #MetaHashCoin (#MHC) -> To ensure consensus, this will be the networks‚Äô digital payment currency. So payments for all network services and self-financing is secured.

The ability to convert any digital asset Ethereum ERC20 (token) into #MHC, transfer it to the network # MetaHash or convert it back.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: These are Decentralized parsers of all popular blockchain platforms. In order for #MetaApps to immediately respond to events in any blockchain system, we will release decentralized parsers allowing the use of API to get balance info and transaction history from wallets across various blockchain platforms. This will allow applications to respond to different blockchain events and verify data accuracy by sending queries to network nodes.

Author: 247mining
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: What is #MetaApps?  This product will be the Decentralised cloud for Real-Time Applications that run on High-Speed, with the ability to handle high loads, shaping the new Decentralised Internet.  With #MetaHash, any program written in any programming language under any operating system can become a decentralised app and work with both data from the internet and data from any blockchain system.  #MetaApps run in real time as regular websites, but they are decentralised and even their creator can‚Äôt change their behaviour unless their users or owners of their digital assets (tokens) cast their votes.  #MetaApps is an evolution of smart contracts and can be used to decentralise any service. These are independent programs that can exist forever and do not belong to anyone.

Body: In order to distribute the coins evenly and there is no situation in which all the coins go into the same hands, 3 equal queues are created. a) For those who want to buy for less than 50 ETH. MHC is accrued for the amount of 50 ETH at the current exchange rate every 4 hours b) For those who want to buy for more than 50 ETH. MHC is accrued for the amount of 50 ETH at the current exchange rate every 4 hours c) A pool for large buyers without queues, but with approval through the Business Development department.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: There will be an interface to delegate coins to a certain address of the node. Just like sending a tx, but without sending coins If a node loses trust, delegation is canceled and you have to delegate again So you don‚Äôt lose coins, but you do lose some rewards until your coins gain trust on another node To gain 100% trust takes 6 months. So after 6 months, you start getting maximum possible rewards.

If you re-delegate your coins from one fair node to another - you don ‚Äòt loose trust The system is meant that you never risk your coins but risk several month of rewards so you pick delegates carefully

Author: 247mining
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: We have an idea we want to discuss with you.  Please tell what you think.  Idea against theft of crypto assets.   Idea abstract example: Smart contract or special wallet with a second signature that can cancel a transaction within a certain period specified by a data-transaction in the network.  Simple example. An exchange creates a wallet where it keeps its assets. It sets 24 hours to cancel any outgoing transaction by an additional password. The second password is stored securely and is not needed until a successful hacker attack happens.  Negative: - you have to wait for 24 hours (or whatever time is specified) - if you lose the second password your assets could be blocked by an attacker, but you keep the password securely stored for emergency and don't have to use it online until it happens  Positive: even if you lose both passwords hacker can't use the funds, it will be a cat and mouse game that will discourage stealing   There can be multiple variations. The same password can make transactions and cancel. MultiPasswords for cancelation are needed. And other. It's cool.  The main disadvantage is that no TX is really committed until X hours passed. For daily traders, this might not be something positive. This mitigates the impact of the hacked exchange risk. The hacking best strategy, in this case, would be to retire small amounts trying to minimize the chance that the exchange realizes it. Other systems use some kind of blacklist to make the hacked assets unusable, but that requires some degree of centralization.

Author: MetaHash
Title: [ANN][ICO]‚ö° Metahash - cryptocurrency for decentralized apps‚ö°
Body: The amount of nodes is limited by a requirement of Coins at Stake lowering the total price of Network Hardware down. Consensus protection lies more on the value of the Coins rather than Nodes. Moreover as the amount of transactions is extremely high when we divide the money people involved in forging by the amount of transactions we'll see that a fee much lower than current blockchains. brings more rewards to people involved in forging as if they would spend the same amount of funds to mining.  A PoW blockchain needs both hardware to calculate hashes and nodes. In PoS network protection lies on Coins themself. And Coin value is not pure speculative, but is dependant from transaction commissions.  About the MVP you can be sure we'll make it public within a few days (or you can have a look at https://github.com/MetaHashOfficial). So, please stay tuned!
